===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ひつじ}}
{{IPAfont|⟨pi<sub>1</sub>tuzi⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/pʲituzi/}}  → {{IPAchar|/ɸituzi/}} → {{IPAchar|/çitsudʑi/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=ひつじ}}.<ref name="JDB">{{R:JDB|page=614}}</ref> Further derivation unknown. Theories include:
* From {{compound|ja|日|tr1=hi|t1=sun|辻|tr2=tsuji|t2=crossroads}}, as the sun begins to set around the hour of the Sheep according to traditional Chinese timekeeping.
* Alteration from {{compound|ja|髭|tr1=hige|t1=facial hair|つ|tr2=tsu|pos2={{der|ja|ojp|-}} possessive particle|牛|tr3=ushi|t3=cattle}}.
* Alteration from {{compound|ja|人|tr1=hito|t1=person|牛|tr2=ushi|t2=cattle}}, literally “people’s cattle”.
* Alteration from {{compound|ja|養す|tr1=hitasu|t1=to raise (cattle)|獣|tr2=shishi|t2=a beast used for its meat}} or {{compound|ja|養し|tr1=hitashi|pos1=the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||stem or continuative form}} of 養す|牛|tr2=ushi|t2=cattle}}. If true, would parallel the supposed development of {{m|ja|やぎ|tr=yagi}} from {{m|ja|野牛|tr=yagyū||wild cattle}}, referring to the relative ease of domestication of sheep.<ref name="">[https://gogen-yurai.jp/hitsuji 語源由来辞典 ''Gogen Yurai Jiten'']</ref>

Might be cognate with {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*fetuzi}}.

